see the blood

00:08:12.720 --> 00:08:14.344 align:middle line:84%
moving through the
embryo of the chick.

00:08:14.344 --> 00:08:17.110 align:middle line:84%
He chose a chick because it's
not attached to its mother,

00:08:17.110 --> 00:08:19.950 align:middle line:84%
so whatever's happening is
not dependent on the mother.

00:08:19.950 --> 00:08:21.620 align:middle line:90%
It's happening in this chick.

00:08:21.620 --> 00:08:23.090 align:middle line:90%
So here's the key.

00:08:23.090 --> 00:08:27.390 align:middle line:84%
The blood is moving
through the embryo

00:08:27.390 --> 00:08:29.970 align:middle line:84%
although the heart
has yet to develop.

00:08:29.970 --> 00:08:32.710 align:middle line:84%
There is no heart
pumping the blood.

00:08:32.710 --> 00:08:34.120 align:middle line:90%
So two questions come up.

00:08:34.120 --> 00:08:36.039 align:middle line:84%
Number one, why is
the blood moving

00:08:36.039 --> 00:08:37.690 align:middle line:90%
