the opportunity

00:13:09.980 --> 00:13:13.950 align:middle line:84%
to stop burning fossil fuels, to
find clean, green, sustainable

00:13:13.950 --> 00:13:15.410 align:middle line:90%
ways of living.

00:13:15.410 --> 00:13:18.220 align:middle line:84%
And that opportunity has been
with us for over 60 years.

00:13:18.220 --> 00:13:20.060 align:middle line:84%
We've had the technology
for over 60 years.

00:13:20.060 --> 00:13:21.570 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: To feed every
human on the planet.

00:13:21.570 --> 00:13:23.630 align:middle line:84%
>>BRADEN: To do that, to feed
every human on the planet.

00:13:23.630 --> 00:13:24.430 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:13:24.430 --> 00:13:27.670 align:middle line:84%
But when it comes to
these cycles of time,

00:13:27.670 --> 00:13:30.080 align:middle line:84%
we are reluctant
sometimes to see them.

00:13:30.080 --> 00:13:32.450 align:middle line:84%
So our ancestors, when
they saw the changes,

00:13:32.450 --> 00:13:34.350 align:middle line:84%
it was less about
healing the earth,

00:13:34.350 --> 00:13:36.200 align:middle line:84%
because they didn't see
the earth as broken.

00:13:36.200 --> 00:13:39.420 align:middle line:84%
It was about them
allowing themselves

00:13:39.420 --> 00:13:42.230 align:middle line:84%
to move in harmony with the
new cycles that were appearing.

00:13:42.230 --> 00:13:47.590 align:middle line:84%
So what that means is that we're
living a time of volatility.

00:13:47.590 --> 00:13:51.890 align:middle line:84%
The convergence of three cycles
in our lifetimes-- climate,

00:13:51.890 --> 00:13:55.100 align:middle line:84%
the economic cycles,
and cycles of conflict--

00:13:55.100 --> 00:13:57.040 align:middle line:84%
that are all governed
by natural rhythms.

00:13:57.040 --> 00:14:00.100 align:middle line:84%
They are all converging in
this little window of time.

00:14:00.100 --> 00:14:03.670 align:middle line:84%
And that is contributing
to the volatility

00:14:03.670 --> 00:14:06.310 align:middle line:84%
of what's happening in
our lives and our world.

00:14:06.310 --> 00:14:08.730 align:middle line:84%
The problem is we've
been conditioned

00:14:08.730 --> 00:14:11.440 align:middle line:84%
to think of ourselves as
separate from the world,

00:14:11.440 --> 00:14:14.620 align:middle line:84%
and we're trying to solve our
problems through separation

00:14:14.620 --> 00:14:16.700 align:middle line:90%
and competition and conflict.

00:14:16.700 --> 00:14:19.780 align:middle line:84%
When the best science,
and our ancestors told us,

00:14:19.780 --> 00:14:22.015 align:middle line:84%
very, very clearly-- science
is telling us today--

00:14:22.015 --> 00:14:23.735 align:middle line:84%
that the fundamental
rule of nature

00:14:23.735 --> 00:14:26.430 align:middle line:90%
is cooperation, not competition.

00:14:26.430 --> 00:14:30.200 align:middle line:84%
And that we are deeply connected
to the world and ourselves,

00:14:30.200 --> 00:14:31.950 align:middle line:84%
not separate as we've
been led to believe.

00:14:31.950 --> 00:14:36.470 align:middle line:84%
And as we shift this
thinking from separation

00:14:36.470 --> 00:14:40.370 align:middle line:84%
to connection, from
competition to cooperation,

00:14:40.370 --> 00:14:43.820 align:middle line:84%
that opens the door
to new opportunities

00:14:43.820 --> 00:14:45.490 align:middle line:90%
of solving the problems.

00:14:45.490 --> 00:14:46.700 align:middle line:90%
The answers are there.

00:14:46.700 --> 00:14:49.800 align:middle line:84%
The key is for us
to find the way

00:14:49.800 --> 00:14:53.820 align:middle line:84%
to shift our thinking to make
it a priority in our lives

00:14:53.820 --> 00:14:56.960 align:middle line:84%
to help one another
and to begin thinking

00:14:56.960 --> 00:14:59.490 align:middle line:84%
in terms of cooperation
rather than competition.

00:14:59.490 --> 00:15:01.360 align:middle line:90%
And that's huge.

00:15:01.360 --> 00:15:02.610 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's the new normal.

